    <section id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <!--<div class="header-content-inner">-->
			<div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 text-center">
                <h2 class="section-heading">What are slim BIM charts?</h2>
                <hr>
                <h4>Slim BIM charts are a visual and numeric method developed by the <a href="http://big.yonsei.ac.kr">building informatics group</a> at Yonsei University for representing the level of BIM adoption and implementation using the four most commonly used variables for measuring the level of BIM adoption and implementation: level of adoption, depth of implementation, level of proficiency, and years using BIM. </h4>
				<br>
				<h4>There are three types of slim BIM charts: diamond chart, ball chart, and triangle chart. The diamond chart uses all four variables. The triangle chart uses three variables except for BIM adoption rate. The ball chart uses only two variables: BIM adoption rate and either one of depth of BIM implementation or level of proficiency.</h4>
				<h4>The areas of a diamond chart, a triangle chart, and a ball chart are called D-value, T-value, and B-value, respectively. For more details on slim BIM charts, please refer to <a href="#">"paper title</a>."</h4>
				<p></p>
                <a href="#chart" class="btn btn-primary btn-xl page-scroll">Slim BIM charts</a>
				<a href="#survey" class="btn btn-primary btn-xl page-scroll">Join our slim BIM survey</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

